ravis Scott,
and she=E2=80=99s truly excited to see what the conversation produces. That=
 may be Cultured=E2=80=99s greatest strength: an unbridled enthusiasm for a=
rtists, dealers, collectors, and how they all fit into a broader culture.

Her beachhead in Los Angeles may not have yielded its own magazine, but Har=
relson hasn=E2=80=99t given up on expansion. In recent years, she began pro=
ducing broadsheet versions of Cultured that are distributed where the art w=
orld congregates during the year=E2=80=94there=E2=80=99s a supplement for A=
rt Basel in Miami Beach, two for the Hamptons, and now one for Aspen=E2=80=
=99s early August art rendezvous. This year, Harrelson organized a series o=
f talks at Anderson Ranch featuring artists, critics, collectors, and even =
Harrelson herself as an interviewer.

When I asked where she might go next, Harrelson mentioned Mexico City, a gr=
owing art capital with its own well-established art fair in February, Zona =
Maco, and numerous gallery and collector exhibition
spaces. There=E2=80=99s also several European cities where Cultured has pro=
mising penetration through subscriptions and newsstand sales. Meanwhile, Ha=
rrelson has been gradually expanding her digital business, creating a web-o=
nly subscription as well as higher priced tiers for print and the V.I.P. Cu=
ltured Club to cultivate a passionate audience she can deliver to business =
partners. There=E2=80=99s also an Instagram account, of course, with 352,00=
0 followers, far behind Artforum and ARTnews=E2=80=99s million-plus followe=
r counts, but not out of the hunt given those two brands=E2=80=99 long head=
 start in name recognition.

Besides being a magazine with a more organic connection with art world audi=
ences, Cultured has the advantage of not being an incumbent in the art medi=
a. Harrelson has been able to build her business with grit, determination, =
and a good sense of where to spend her money for the most effect. With so m=
any deep-pocketed corporate competitors=E2=80=94we
haven=E2=80=99t even discussed the gallery-sponsored magazines=E2=80=94Cult=
ured=E2=80=99s rise has been an unexpected but welcome surprise.

